Key Match Events: Zhang Yuning had two consecutive strikes saved by the Lebanese goalkeeper in the 45th minute.
Lebanon hit the woodwork twice, once in the 45th minute and again in the 52nd minute.
Wu Lei had a close-range shot cleared by the goalkeeper in the 65th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Chinese head coach Aleksandar Jankovic made two changes to his starting lineup, replacing Tan Long and Wang Qiuming with Zhang Yuning and Xu Xin.
Jankovic acknowledged the team's nervousness in the opening match and emphasized the importance of controlling possession.
Post-Match Reflections: Jankovic praised the team's mental strength and attitude despite the goalless draw.
He acknowledged the team's missed chances and stated that controlling the game and dealing with stress were key aspects of their performance.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Both teams had several chances but were unable to convert them into goals.
Lebanon's goalkeeper Ostafa Matar made crucial saves to keep the game goalless.
